\begin_layout Standard
As we can see, as 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon$
\end_inset

 increases more runs are unable to reach the right answer, and tend to fail.
 This makes seance as 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon$
\end_inset

 represents the probability of error.
 In addition the runs that do fail have a larger Hamming distance as 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon$
\end_inset

 increases - 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon=0.06$
\end_inset

 had a maximal distance of 30, 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon=0.08$
\end_inset

 had 40, and 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon=0.1$
\end_inset

 had 60, which too makes seance.
\end_layout

